 JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa has spoken against judging the victims of the Enyobeni tavern tragedy. He says he is heartbroken about the losses and sent his condolences to their families. WATCH | Mass funeral for Enyobeni tavern victims Ramaphosa says there is an urgent need to save the youth of South Africa. "Our hearts are broken. We have lost our children here. There are parents who will not get to hug or kiss their son or daughter again, and there are grandparents who will not be blessed to see their grandson or granddaughter growing up and having their own families," he said. Ramaphosa delivered the eulogy at a mass funeral on Wednesday.  President Cyril Ramaphosa says children should not be allowed at taverns and sold alcohol. Twenty-one teenagers died at Enyobeni tavern in East London. #eNCA #DStv403